<div id="review_2491382" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2491382" />
    <a title="Maya" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35751-maya"><img alt="Maya" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1174964593p2/35751.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2491382?book_show_action=true">Jun 28, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maya" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maya" href="/user/show/35751-maya">Maya</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35751-maya?shelf=garciamarquez">garciamarquez</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35751-maya?shelf=myfavorites">myfavorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2491382" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5349129101376049752">Read this during my rabid Garcia Marquez consumption of last year and it&apos;s one of the only short story collections that I actually enjoyed. Usually, I can&apos;t get into short stories, I always find the character development lacking and then just can&apos;t relate, plus I always feel cheated at the end on the occasions that I did enjoy the story because I want more. But, I think that <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/search/search?q=%20Gabriel%20Garcia%20Marquez' title=' Gabriel Garcia Marquez' rel='nofollow noopener'> Gabriel Garcia Marquez</a> is simply so good at storytelling he can wrap the whole story up in a tiny package and have it sta</span>
  <span id="freeText5349129101376049752" style="display:none">Read this during my rabid Garcia Marquez consumption of last year and it's one of the only short story collections that I actually enjoyed. Usually, I can't get into short stories, I always find the character development lacking and then just can't relate, plus I always feel cheated at the end on the occasions that I did enjoy the story because I want more. But, I think that <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/search/search?q=%20Gabriel%20Garcia%20Marquez" title=" Gabriel Garcia Marquez" rel="nofollow noopener"> Gabriel Garcia Marquez</a> is simply so good at storytelling he can wrap the whole story up in a tiny package and have it stand up to his more epic works. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5349129101376049752" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


