<span id="freeTextContainer10229255550062558059">I’m at the point in the pandemic where I’m asking my close friends about books that fundamentally changed their feelings about reading- that book that has stayed with throughout the years. <br/><br/>This was my friends Sarah’s choice. Now, I tend not to read short stories, because I get invested in a story and *poof* it’s over and my heart and mind aren’t ready to move on. <br/><br/>But it’s been years since I’ve read short stories so I thought I’d give it a try again. <br/><br/>RESULTS:<br/>- I still prefer longer stories. This </span>
  <span id="freeText10229255550062558059" style="display:none">I’m at the point in the pandemic where I’m asking my close friends about books that fundamentally changed their feelings about reading- that book that has stayed with throughout the years. <br /><br />This was my friends Sarah’s choice. Now, I tend not to read short stories, because I get invested in a story and *poof* it’s over and my heart and mind aren’t ready to move on. <br /><br />But it’s been years since I’ve read short stories so I thought I’d give it a try again. <br /><br />RESULTS:<br />- I still prefer longer stories. This felt like a creative snapshot portfolio. Interesting to see this level of brainstorming.<br /><br />- There was really interesting worlds/ bits in here. Some felt like comedy bits. Some felt like thriller bits. <br /><br />- The feminist part of my brain scoffed at lines that didn’t age well. <br /><br />- Glad I read it to connect with my friend but meh- unsure if it will have a long lasting positive impression on me. <br /></span>
